You can encrypt your messages using a secret key. Only people who know this key will be able to decrypt them. No Chat Reports will automatically decrypt all encrypted messages when suitable key is provided and feature is enabled.
However, be aware that encryption is not a "magic wand" kind of solution. Moderators on third-party servers can mute or ban you for sending what will appear to them as garbled mess in chat. Futhermore, it is recommended that you generate custom encryption key, and communicate it to other people only via secure channels. Click "Learn More" to learn more about how and when you should use encryption.

§eProfile: §oSituational Cooling (High)§r
More powerful load suppression depending on the situation. (For weak PC.) In addition to the behavior of Eco profile, FPS will be limited to 30fps when the character is stationary, in inventory screen or in any GUI screen.
languages.ja_jp:
§e一括設定: §oクールダウン(強)§r

languages.en_us:
§eProfile: §oSituational Cooling (Low)§r
Proactively control the load depending on the situation. (For PC that runs at 60fps or higher.) In addition to the behavior of Eco profile, FPS will be limited to 60fps when the character is stationary, in inventory screen or in any GUI screen. Depending on VSync and Max Framerate settings in the Video Settings, the effect will be less effective.
languages.ja_jp:
§e一括設定: §oクールダウン(弱)§r
状況に応じて積極的に負荷抑制を行います(60fps以上出るPC向け)。ECO設定の動作に加え、キャラクタが静止した場合やインベントリやGUI画面を開いている場合に、フレームレートを60fpsに制限します。ビデオ設定の垂直同期や最大フレームレートの設定によっては効果が出にくくなります。

languages.en_us: A single pixel on the map can contain multiple transparent layers and an opaque block under them. The deposits of Ore found around your world are nothing new to you. What you have so far left out of consideration though are mineral veins, which contain a mix of different ores. Due to their wide and thin spread, the average miner can't find them, but a might be able to assist with that. <&drill>To find and determine minerals in the world, you will want to craft a Core Sample Drill. Supply the machine with power and rightclick it or use redstone to activate it. It drills into the chunk and extracts a core sample which shows if and what mineral was found and its yield. The Drill consumes Flux/t and takes ticks to fully retrieve and analyse a sample.

The sample can also be placed as a block by sneaking and rightclicking. Using a map on the sample block will set a marker for the chunk.

The following pages list every type of vein and the ores that can be retrieved from them.

Wild Whirlisprigs can be befriended and will drop Whirlisprig Shards if a tree is grown near them.
